<p>Losing a family member is a deeply personal tragedy.  Your words of support can help carry them through this difficult period.  Here are some messages to express your sympathy:</p>
<li> My deepest condolences on your loss.  May God grant you peace and comfort.</li>
<li> Thinking of you and your family during this difficult time.</li>
<li> Words cannot express how saddened I am to hear about your loss.</li>
<li> Please accept my heartfelt sympathy. Your loved one will be deeply missed.</li>
<li> May God bless you and your family during this time of sorrow.</li>
<li> Praying for strength and peace for you and your family.</li>
<li> I am so sorry for your loss.  May God welcome your loved one into His loving embrace.</li>
<li> Your family is in my thoughts and prayers.</li>
<li> May the love and memories of your loved one bring you comfort.</li>
<li> With deepest sympathy, I offer my prayers and support.</li>
<li> Sending love and prayers to you and your family.  May your hearts find peace.</li>
<li> Holding you and your family in my heart during this time of grief.</li>
<li> May God grant you the strength you need to face this difficult time.</li>
<li> I am so sorry for your loss. May your loved one rest in eternal peace.</li>
<li> Please know that I'm here for you and your family if you need anything at all.</li>
    

